data.enText: patterns that are sewn onto cloth using threads of various colours; cloth that is decorated in this way
the skill or activity of decorating cloth in this way

simple_means.memory_skill: em 使… + broid〔= braid〕扭 + ery 表行为 → 使〔线〕缠结在一起 → 刺绣

tr: elaboration of an interpretation by the use of decorative (sometimes fictitious) detail
example: the mystery has been heightened by many embellishments in subsequent retellings

value.def: Embroidery consists of designs stitched into cloth.

example.ex: The shorts had blue embroidery over the pockets...
example.tran: 这条短裤的口袋上有蓝色刺绣。

value.def: Embroidery is the activity of stitching designs onto cloth.

example.ex: She learned sewing, knitting and embroidery.
example.tran: 她学了缝纫、编织和刺绣。

partsOfSpeech.d: 编成辫子（把头发扭在一起）

partsOfSpeech.dec: em 使… + broid〔= braid〕扭 + ery 表行为 → 使〔线〕缠结在一起 → 刺绣
up 向上 + braid 扭 → 向上抓辫子 → 谴责
